trade.nonStocksAndnonBullPointDesc: a pip value that represents the amount of profit and loss that can be obtained if the quote fluctuates by 1 pip when holding a 1 lot.  Example: Buy 1 lot of EURUSD, up from 1.12930 to 1.12940(volatility 1 pip) and get a $10 gain.
trade.stocksPointDesc: a pip value that represents the amount of profit or loss that can be obtained if the quote fluctuates by 1 pip when holding a 1 lot. Example: Buy 1 lot stock, from 69 to 70(volatility 10 pips), and get a $1 gain.
trade.bullBearPointDesc: a pip value that represents the amount of profit or loss that can be obtained if the quote fluctuates by 1 pip when holding a 1 lot. Example: Buy 1 lot of EURUSD bull/bear options, open at 79, and rise to 80(volatility 1 pip) for a $1 gain.
trade.priceIntroContent: After setting the order price, the pending order will be closed at the market price only if the market price reaches that order price.
trade.collecPriceError: Collect price is too close to the market price, please select the available collect price
trade.estMarginContent:
Bull bear options , margin used = open position price x 1 lot value x lots. When you open a position, it means that the "marign used" and "maximum loss" have been determined.

1）when the market price does not touch the collect price：
- profit and loss =（closing price-opening price）x 1 lot value x lots，that mean is not touching the collect price to close the position, return the bull and bear premium；

2）When the market hits the collect price：
- profit and loss = margin used（in this case, closing price = 0），when the collect price is touched, the position is liquidated and the bull-bear premium is deducted.

when the collect price is touched，“Profit and loss”will be settled at the real-time exchange rate，for reference only
trade.estMarginDesc: Expect margin，means the margin held on the position（weekends and holidays will be based on holiday margin setting)；If hold positions in both directions at the same time, only the margin with the largest position is calculated.
trade.volumeExplain1: A lot value that represents the amount of profit and loss that can be obtained if the quote fluctuates by 1 pip when holding a 1 lot. Example: Buy 1 lot of EURUSD bull/bear options, open at 79 and rise to 80(volatility 1 point) for a $1 gain. Contract point value=1 pip value x lot.
trade.volumeExplain2: A lot value that represents the amount of profit and loss that can be obtained if the quote fluctuates by 1 pip when holding a 1 lot. Example: Buy 1 lot and fight more, from 69 to 70(volatility 10 points), and get a $1 gain. Contract point value=1 point value x lot.
trade.volumeExplain3: A lot value that represents the amount of profit and loss that can be obtained if the quote fluctuates by 1 pip when holding a 1 lot. Example: Buy 1 lot of EURUSD,upfrom 1.12930 to 1.12940(volatility 1 point) and get a $10 gain. Contract point value=1 point value x lot.

trade.availableLoanContent3: Your account balance is insufficient and has available amount to borrow, and the system will automatically offer the loan and trade when placing an order. Interest is calculated from the order is executed, the platform charges interest by hour, interest will be count as an hour even less than one hour. Borrowing Interest=Borrowed Amount *（Daily Interest Rate/24）* Borrowing Hours，Daily Interest Rate{0}。
